WEBVTT

00:01.484 --> 00:03.103
<i>There are people in this world</i>

00:03.170 --> 00:05.655
<i>who would rather destroy</i>
<i>than create,</i>

00:05.723 --> 00:07.457
<i>rather take than give.</i>

00:07.525 --> 00:09.542
<i>These people must be stopped.</i>

00:11.000 --> 00:17.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:24.074 --> 00:25.074
Ugh!

00:25.126 --> 00:27.243
Ouch!
Brooke, what the hell?!

00:28.379 --> 00:29.912
Was I sleep-fighting
again?

00:29.964 --> 00:31.131
Yes.

00:31.215 --> 00:33.133
No more "Kick-Ass"
for my wife before bed.

00:34.835 --> 00:36.936
You said "wife."

00:37.021 --> 00:38.638
I love hearing that.

00:40.558 --> 00:42.142
Mm.
Where you going?

00:42.226 --> 00:44.627
Work. I'm directing
a commercial today. Remember?

00:44.695 --> 00:45.729
No!

00:45.796 --> 00:47.313
So now
the honeymoon's over,

00:47.398 --> 00:49.616
and we're just gonna turn into
a boring, old married couple?

00:49.700 --> 00:51.151
Uh, you fight in your sleep,
Brooke.

00:51.235 --> 00:52.952
Any couple you're a part of
couldn't be boring.

00:54.104 --> 00:56.873
What am I supposed to do
without you?

00:56.940 --> 00:58.107
I don't know.

00:58.159 --> 01:00.076
Go to the grocery store?
Run errands? Cook?

01:01.612 --> 01:05.165
Things a boring, old husband
would say for $500, please.

01:05.248 --> 01:07.050
Or you could
watch "Kick-Ass" again.

01:08.586 --> 01:09.669
We have a winner.

01:14.625 --> 01:17.010
Breakfast?
What's the special occasion?

01:17.094 --> 01:19.396
Marvin's first day
back in television.

01:19.463 --> 01:21.130
Yep,
I have come full circle

01:21.182 --> 01:23.099
and ended up
back at the bottom.

01:23.150 --> 01:25.301
There's nothing wrong
with starting over.

01:25.352 --> 01:26.853
Julian
wouldn't have hired you

01:26.937 --> 01:28.321
if he didn't think
you were talented.

01:28.406 --> 01:29.472
I'm proud of you.

01:29.523 --> 01:31.941
Anyway, I should
probably head home.

01:31.992 --> 01:33.076
I'll see you tonight?

01:33.143 --> 01:34.327
Bye.

01:36.597 --> 01:37.947
You do know
it's kind of mean

01:37.998 --> 01:39.616
to make her do the walk of shame
every day, right?

01:40.868 --> 01:42.285
When are you two
moving back in together?

01:42.336 --> 01:44.337
We're taking it slow.
Man, "slow"?

01:44.422 --> 01:46.122
If you go any slower,
you're gonna be going backwards.

01:46.173 --> 01:47.624
What you gonna do,
take her on a date

01:47.675 --> 01:49.876
and try to figure out what her
favorite flavor of ice cream is?

01:49.960 --> 01:50.877
It's rocky road.

01:50.961 --> 01:52.378
And I don't think

01:52.463 --> 01:54.214
that <i>you</i> should be giving
relationship advice.

01:54.298 --> 01:56.599
You wanted to propose to
Nathan's mom on your third date.

01:56.667 --> 02:01.504
♪ You had your young mind
in the gutter ♪

02:01.555 --> 02:08.094
♪ you had your feet
on the ground ♪

02:08.162 --> 02:10.179
♪ see you on the way up ♪

02:10.231 --> 02:12.398
Damn. You're good.

02:12.483 --> 02:13.683
I know.

02:13.734 --> 02:15.985
It's still nice
to hear.

02:16.036 --> 02:18.321
You want to know which
picture is my favorite? Hmm?

02:21.358 --> 02:22.559
<i>You</i> took that one.

02:22.626 --> 02:24.544
Did I?
Oh, that's right -- I did.

02:24.628 --> 02:26.379
I had forgotten
'cause it was just so easy.

02:26.464 --> 02:27.747
All I had to do
was point and click.

02:27.832 --> 02:30.032
Mm. That's 'cause I set
my camera to "idiot mode."

02:30.084 --> 02:31.918
Hey, there's no need
to be nasty.

02:32.002 --> 02:34.337
You're probably
a better photographer than I am.

02:34.388 --> 02:35.872
There's just
no way to tell.

02:35.923 --> 02:37.206
Oh, yes, there is.

02:37.258 --> 02:39.642
I've gotten three job offers
since posting these.

02:39.710 --> 02:41.845
Did you --
did you post the one I took?

02:41.896 --> 02:43.813
Just because those offers
may have been for <i>me.</i>

02:43.881 --> 02:45.348
Hmm.
Maybe they were.

02:47.017 --> 02:50.270
Let's go do something fun today
Like bungee jumping.

02:50.354 --> 02:51.488
Let's go bungee jumping.

02:51.555 --> 02:52.856
No way.

02:52.907 --> 02:55.325
You see, I have a strict policy
against doing anything

02:55.392 --> 02:57.443
where people won't feel sorry
for you if you die.

02:57.528 --> 02:59.279
For example,
you'll never hear anyone say,

02:59.363 --> 03:00.613
"oh, that poor guy.

03:00.698 --> 03:02.332
"He just wanted to tie a rope
around his ankles

03:02.399 --> 03:04.250
and jump off a bridge."

03:04.335 --> 03:07.670
Okay, maybe not <i>that,</i>
<i>but something thrilling.</i>

03:07.738 --> 03:09.622
Hmm.

03:09.707 --> 03:11.073
I think
I know what you need.

03:13.010 --> 03:14.794
Uh --

03:19.800 --> 03:22.986
What's the answer, dummy?

03:23.053 --> 03:25.605
It's "Tommy." And you didn't
ask me a question.

03:25.689 --> 03:29.108
Fat, drunk, and stupid is no way
to go through life, son.

03:29.193 --> 03:31.761
How are you going to
practice business law

03:31.829 --> 03:34.931
if you can't predict
my questions ahead of time?

03:34.982 --> 03:37.116
I just
don't understand.

03:37.201 --> 03:40.269
Maybe you'll understand <i>this.</i>

03:43.273 --> 03:46.776
♪ Ask me to fetch your crown ♪

03:49.213 --> 03:50.780
Come on, man.
That didn't happen.

03:50.831 --> 03:52.916
Plus, you're quoting lines
from "Animal House."

03:52.967 --> 03:54.834
Okay, maybe I exaggerated
a <i>little.</i>

03:54.919 --> 03:56.419
But the guy
is a nightmare.

03:56.470 --> 03:58.555
He gets off
on humiliating everyone.

03:58.622 --> 04:01.307
Eh, so study. I mean, he can't make you
look stupid if you know the material.

04:01.392 --> 04:03.643
And, besides, I mean,
didn't you take this guy's class

04:03.727 --> 04:05.144
'cause it was tough?

04:05.229 --> 04:06.846
I don't have a problem
with him being tough.

04:06.931 --> 04:08.348
I have a problem
with him being a bully.

04:08.432 --> 04:10.400
Mm, it <i>is</i> his class.

04:10.467 --> 04:12.518
Look, you got
one of two options --

04:12.603 --> 04:14.821
either switch professors
or deal with it.

04:14.905 --> 04:16.439
It's too late to switch.

04:16.490 --> 04:18.440
Well, then
"deal with it" wins.

04:18.492 --> 04:20.276
Otherwise,
you can't be an Agent.

04:27.284 --> 04:29.485
Chase isn't here.

04:29.536 --> 04:31.487
Oh,
and the cease-fire is off

04:31.538 --> 04:33.122
because you kissed him
during our truce.

04:33.173 --> 04:35.258
And you slept with him
during the reception.

04:35.325 --> 04:37.460
But it doesn't matter.
I'm not here for Chase.

04:37.511 --> 04:39.178
He suddenly
seemed less attractive

04:39.263 --> 04:40.546
when I saw him
in the limo

04:40.614 --> 04:42.382
with a 5-foot hairy mole
attached to him.

04:43.684 --> 04:45.885
Anyway, I wanted
to talk to Haley

04:45.970 --> 04:47.720
about
recording a song here.

04:47.805 --> 04:50.306
Since when do you sing?

04:50.374 --> 04:51.691
I'm serious.

04:51.775 --> 04:54.143
I know.
That's why I'm laughing.

04:54.194 --> 04:56.145
Well, like I said,
I came to ask Haley, not you.

04:56.196 --> 04:59.148
Why talk to the greasy rag when
you can talk to the mechanic?

05:04.538 --> 05:06.039
Haley thinks
what <i>I</i> think.

05:07.625 --> 05:08.541
We'll see.

05:08.626 --> 05:10.026
Okay, then. Bye.

05:15.032 --> 05:18.167
<i>Evil lurks</i>
<i>behind every door in Tree Hill.</i>

05:18.218 --> 05:22.105
<i>Stay tuned, loyal viewers...</i>
<i>To be dazzled.</i>

05:27.127 --> 05:29.512
♪ I don't want to be anything ♪

05:29.563 --> 05:33.049
♪ other than what I've been
trying to be lately ♪

05:33.100 --> 05:35.568
♪ all I have to do
is think of me ♪

05:35.653 --> 05:39.221
♪ and I have peace of mind ♪

05:39.273 --> 05:41.157
♪ I'm tired
of looking 'round rooms ♪

05:41.224 --> 05:42.525
♪ wondering what I gotta do ♪

05:42.576 --> 05:45.061
♪ or who I'm supposed to be ♪

05:45.112 --> 05:47.497
♪ I don't want to be anything ♪

05:47.564 --> 05:49.582
♪ other than me ♪

